observations.recommendation:
We recommend that Management:
a.	Refrain from granting benefits or bonuses without a firm legal basis to prevent audit disallowances from illegal disbursement of public funds;
b.	Submit legal basis in the granting of Other Personnel Benefits of P15,000.00 per official/ employee or refund the full amount thereof.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor and the Municipal Accountant:

a.	Strictly require officials and employees to liquidate their cash advances within the prescribed period to avoid the accumulation of outstanding balances pursuant to 5.1 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;

b.	Issue a demand letter to officials and employees especially those who are still in active service to settle their overdue accounts. Otherwise, effect the withholding of salaries pursuant to 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 until such time that the cash advances are fully settled. For employees who are no longer connected with the Municipal Government, issue collection letters to them or to their relatives to recover the amounts due from them;

c.	Send a follow-up letter to COA – ICFAU to ascertain the status of previously submitted liquidation documents for charges against previous years’ confidential fund and request issuance of credit advice or credit notice; and

d.	File request for authority to write-off dormant or long outstanding unliquidated cash advances, if necessary, to the Office of the Auditor pursuant to COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We recommend that Municipal Accountant:

Evaluate the actual work assignment to address the imbalance of duties and responsibilities between permanent and casual plantilla personnel in the Acctg, Office;
Distribute workloads properly to Accounting personnel and set deadlines in order to submit financial reports within the period required by law;
Submit on time all monthly and quarterly reports, bank reconciliation statements and Status of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations, Balance Sheet, Statement of Income and Statement of Cash Flows.

Unjustified failure on the part of employee or official concerned to submit the documents and reports shall be a ground for the automatic suspension of payment of his/her salary until he/she shall have complied with the aforesaid requirements without prejudice to any disciplinary action that maybe instituted against him/her.

